<p>A claim is made, a first decision follows, a refusal can be appealed, and throughout that
time a person may be receiving support. Each stage is counted separately, on its own basis,
at its own moment. A figure from one stage tells you very little about another.</p>

<div class="scroll-x">
<table>
  <caption>The asylum system, stage by stage, as at the latest published figures</caption>
  <thead><tr><th scope="col">Stage</th><th scope="col">Latest figure</th><th scope="col">What it counts</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><th scope="row">Claims made</th><td>{% figure "asylum/asylum-applications" %} people</td><td>A flow over the year ending March 2026. Relates to {% figure "asylum/asylum-applications-main-applicants" %} main-applicant applications</td></tr>
    <tr><th scope="row">Awaiting a first decision</th><td>{% figure "asylum/asylum-backlog-people-awaiting-an-initial-decision" %} people</td><td>A stock at 31 March 2026, not an annual intake</td></tr>
    <tr><th scope="row">Decisions issued</th><td>{% figure "asylum/asylum-initial-decisions-total" %} people</td><td>Grants plus refusals over the year. Excludes withdrawals</td></tr>
    <tr><th scope="row">Appealing a refusal</th><td>{% figure "asylum/asylum-appeals-backlog" %} cases</td><td>A different queue, from a different publisher, at a record high</td></tr>
    <tr><th scope="row">Receiving support</th><td>{% figure "asylum/people-in-receipt-of-asylum-support" %} people</td><td>A stock at 31 March 2026, including people at every stage above</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
</div>

<p>Those five numbers cannot be added, subtracted or compared with one another. Three are
stocks and two are flows; four are on the people basis and one, the appeals queue, is on
the cases basis; and that one also comes from a different publisher on a different cycle. See
<a href="/what-the-words-mean/#flow-and-stock">flow and stock</a> and
<a href="/what-the-words-mean/#people-and-cases">people and cases</a>.</p>

