<p>A refusal at first decision is not the end. The grant rate measured at final outcome,
after appeals, has historically run 17 to 29 percentage points higher. Neither
<a href="/common-claims/refused-asylum-seekers-are-eventually-recognised/">"almost all
refusals are overturned"</a> nor "a refusal settles it" survives contact with that.</p>

